3rd consecutive 3 wicket haul for R Ali.
2nd lowest score ever by West Indies (Lowest is 87 v AUS at Sydney 1992/93), 4th lowest by any team in the World Cup.
1st ever win in 7 ODIs at Pune by the team batting first.
1st ever win by Kenya in official ODIs.
1st time West Indies has lost an official ODI to an ICC Associate.
4th win in ODI history by an ICC Associate (all in World Cups, SL v IND 1979, ZIM v AUS 1983, ZIM v ENG 1992).

milestones.description: Hitesh Modi and Thomas Odoyo's 44-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 15 between Tito Odumbe and Aasif Karim
Hitesh Modi and Aasif Karim's 29-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 25 between Odumbe and Martin Suji
Steve Tikolo has broken the record for most sixes (2) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Otieno's 1
Tariq Iqbal has broken the record for most dismissals (2) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Otieno's 1
Rajab Ali has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (5) for KENYA, going past Chudasama
Tariq Iqbal has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (2) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Otieno's 1
